The paper discusses the challenge of monitoring and managing real-time prediction quality in machine learning pipeline deployments, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. The proposed solution involves using an ML algorithm to track the performance of models in deployment, which falls under the category of machine learning algorithms and techniques (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of metrics like accuracy and RMSE, which are commonly used in the evaluation of machine learning models (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of monitoring and management techniques, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of data structures and algorithms to facilitate the monitoring and management of machine learning models, which is relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The mention of computer vision (cs.CV) is less likely, as the paper does not focus on image or video data.
